race.comment: MASTER GEE (6) showed good early dash and stalked the pace last start before drawing clear to score with a bit in hand at Inverell. Bullock's booking adds confidence and he can go back-to-back. ENSIGN PARKER (2) has been in good form, scoring three back at Beaumont (Newcastle) then placing twice in a row. Kept fresh with 33 days between and is right up to this. BRIGHELLA (10) finished third last start over 1300m at this track when he made late ground. Cherry-ripe now and should be about the money. CABSAV (4) warmed nicely late when resuming at Inverell, behind MASTER GEE. Better for that and can play a more significant role this time.
